headline: Workday forecasts fourth-quarter subscription revenue below estimates as client spending weakens
summary: Workday forecast fourth-quarter subscription revenue below Wall Street expectations on Tuesday, hit by weaker client spending on its human capital management software. Shares of the Pleasanton, California-based company fell over 10% in extended trading. Workday is experiencing weak demand for its payroll software, as clients cut tech budgets due to high interest rates and a cooling labor market.
